## 2. Iteration 1 Changes

### RESOLVED - GAP-01: RegisterDeviceRequest Type Fixed
- Added `equipmentType?` and `online?` to `RegisterDeviceRequest` interface
- File: `frontend/src/types/device.types.ts`

### RESOLVED - GAP-02: WebSocket Already Implemented (Analysis Error)
- `useWebSocket.ts` composable exists with full event handling
- `App.vue` calls `connect()` on auth state change
- Supports: `sensor:update`, `device:status`, `automation:executed`, `notification:new`

### RESOLVED - GAP-05: Sensor Components Kept for Future Use
- `BaseSensorCard.vue`, `TemperatureSensor.vue` kept as reusable templates
- Not dead code but reserved for future sensor-specific UI enhancements

### RESOLVED - GAP-06: Automation Runner Uses Dynamic Evaluation
- Runner reads conditions dynamically from `ConditionGroup.conditions[].field`
- All sensor types (temperature, humidity, co2, light, soil_moisture, ph, ec) are supported
- `between` operator properly handled in condition evaluator

### RESOLVED - GAP-08: Sensor Data Collection Cron Added
- New `SensorCollectorService` with 5-minute cron job
- Collects data from all online sensors via Tuya API
- Stores to `sensor_data` TimescaleDB hypertable
- Broadcasts via WebSocket for real-time updates
- File: `backend/src/modules/sensors/sensor-collector.service.ts`

### RESOLVED - GAP-10: Global Error Handler Added
- Axios response interceptor now shows toast notifications for 500/403/404 errors
- Uses `notification.store` for consistent UX
- File: `frontend/src/api/client.ts`

